                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 9.333,
                                "byte_start": 28672,
                                "byte_stop": 66079,
                                "text": "The judgment and opinion of the Court in 73-1309, Bigelow against Virginia will be announced by Mr. Justice Blackmun."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 9.333,
                        "stop": 215.369,
                        "byte_start": 66079,
                        "byte_stop": 890190,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15045,
                            "name": "Harry A. Blackmun",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/harry_a_blackmun",
                            "last_name": "Blackmun",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2689,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 13755600,
                                    "date_end": 775890000,
                                    "appointing_president": "Richard Nixon",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2689"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32712,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 50281,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/harry_a_blackmun.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 8821,
                            "identifier": "harry_a_blackmun"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 9.333,
                                "stop": 15.52,
                                "byte_start": 66079,
                                "byte_stop": 90843,
                                "text": "This case comes to us on appeal from the Supreme Court of the Commonwealth, Virginia."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 15.52,
                                "stop": 23.037,
                                "byte_start": 90843,
                                "byte_stop": 120832,
                                "text": "The appellant, Mr. Bigelow is the managing editor of a weekly newspaper published in Charlottesville."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 23.037,
                                "stop": 33.259,
                                "byte_start": 120832,
                                "byte_stop": 161792,
                                "text": "In 1971, over four years ago, an issue of the newspaper, carried an advertisement by the Women\u0027s Pavilion in New York City."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 33.259,
                                "stop": 47.503,
                                "byte_start": 161792,
                                "byte_stop": 218739,
                                "text": "Its gist was that abortions are now legal in New York and that the advertiser could make all arrangements and help with information and counseling with respect to placement in accredited hospitals and clinics."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 47.503,
                                "stop": 59.875,
                                "byte_start": 218739,
                                "byte_stop": 268267,
                                "text": "At the time the ad was carried, abortions were legal in New York although not in Virginia and there then was no proscription in New York against the rendition of medical referral services for a fee."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 59.875,
                                "stop": 64.678,
                                "byte_start": 268267,
                                "byte_stop": 287389,
                                "text": "Later, the latter was restricted by New York statute."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 64.678,
                                "stop": 81.587,
                                "byte_start": 287389,
                                "byte_stop": 355098,
                                "text": "Also at the time, the advertisement was carried in Virginia, that state had a statute providing that if any person by advertisement or by the circulation of any publication in any manner encourage the procuring of abortion, he was guilty of misdemeanor."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 81.587,
                                "stop": 85.663,
                                "byte_start": 355098,
                                "byte_stop": 371399,
                                "text": "This was an old statute going back to 1878."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 85.663,
                                "stop": 91.764,
                                "byte_start": 371399,
                                "byte_stop": 395745,
                                "text": "Apparently however, Bigelow\u0027s prosecution was the first under that statute in modern times."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 91.764,
                                "stop": 102.699,
                                "byte_start": 395745,
                                "byte_stop": 439526,
                                "text": "And parenthetically, we note that the statute was amended in 1972 so as to restrict its application with respect to an abortion to be performed in Virginia."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 102.699,
                                "stop": 106.614,
                                "byte_start": 439526,
                                "byte_stop": 455199,
                                "text": "Bigelow was found guilty under the statute and was fined."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 106.614,
                                "stop": 112.5,
                                "byte_start": 455199,
                                "byte_stop": 478710,
                                "text": "The Supreme Court of Virginia on review, affirm the conviction by a divided vote."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 112.5,
                                "stop": 122.963,
                                "byte_start": 478710,
                                "byte_stop": 520610,
                                "text": "After the decisions in the abortion cases in this Court, some two years ago, we vacated the judgment and remanded the case for further consideration in the light of those cases."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 122.963,
                                "stop": 128.779,
                                "byte_start": 520610,
                                "byte_stop": 543807,
                                "text": "On reconsideration, the Supreme Court of Virginia again affirmed the conviction."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 128.779,
                                "stop": 135.334,
                                "byte_start": 543807,
                                "byte_stop": 570034,
                                "text": "This of course is a First Amendment case rather than a case concerning abortions as such."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 135.334,
                                "stop": 140.359,
                                "byte_start": 570034,
                                "byte_stop": 590200,
                                "text": "In an opinion filed today, we reverse the judgment of the Supreme Court of Virginia."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 140.359,
                                "stop": 149.852,
                                "byte_start": 590200,
                                "byte_stop": 628130,
                                "text": "We hold that the statute as applied to appellant, Bigelow infringed constitutionally protected speech under the First Amendment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 149.852,
                                "stop": 159.227,
                                "byte_start": 628130,
                                "byte_stop": 665642,
                                "text": "We further hold that the Virginia courts erred in assuming that advertising, as such, was entitled to no First Amendment protection."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 159.227,
                                "stop": 176.415,
                                "byte_start": 665642,
                                "byte_stop": 734396,
                                "text": "Speech is not entirely stripped the First Amendment protection merely because it appears in the form of a paid commercial advertisement and the fact that the ad here, reflected the advertiser\u0027s commercial interests did not negate all First Amendment guarantees."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 176.415,
                                "stop": 182.446,
                                "byte_start": 734396,
                                "byte_stop": 758533,
                                "text": "Viewed in its entirety, this ad conveyed information of potential interest to a diverse audience."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 182.446,
                                "stop": 186.835,
                                "byte_start": 758533,
                                "byte_stop": 776088,
                                "text": "The State of course, has an interest in the welfare and health of its citizens."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 186.835,
                                "stop": 194.661,
                                "byte_start": 776088,
                                "byte_stop": 807330,
                                "text": "It may seek to disseminate information so as to enable its citizens to make better informed decisions when they leave the borders of the state."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 194.661,
                                "stop": 206.876,
                                "byte_start": 807330,
                                "byte_stop": 856231,
                                "text": "But it may not, under the guise of exercising internal police powers, bar a citizen of another State from disseminating information about activity that is legal in that other State."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 206.876,
                                "stop": 215.369,
                                "byte_start": 856231,
                                "byte_stop": 890190,
                                "text": "I\u0027m authorized to say that Mr. Justice Rehnquist has filed a dissenting opinion and is joined in that opinion by Mr. Justice White."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
